cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about using deep learning for brain tumour segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel architecture for deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for segmentation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence). The proposed architecture involves leveraging deep features within or across modalities, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE - Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with multimodal imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM - Multimedia).
